SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04486432
Version: 1

HPSBHF03151 rev.1 - HP Integrated Lights-Out 2 and 4 (iLO 2, iLO 4), Chassis
Management (iLO CM), Remote Denial of Service, Remote Execution of Code,
Elevation of Privilege

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2015-03-17
Last Updated: 2015-03-17

Potential Security Impact: Remote Denial of Service, remote execution of
code, elevation of privilege

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP Integrated
Lights-Out 2 and 4 (iLO 2, iLO 4) and Chassis Management (iLO CM) firmware.
The vulnerabilities could be exploited remotely resulting in Denial of
Service (DoS) remote execution of code, and elevation of privilege

References:

CVE-2014-7876 (SSRT101745)

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.

HP Integrated Lights-Out 2 (iLO 2) firmware versions prior to v2.27

HP Integrated Lights-Out 4 (iLO 4) firmware versions prior to v2.03

HP iLO Chassis Management (iLO CM) firmware versions prior to v1.30

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2014-7876    (AV:N/AC:H/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       7.6
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP has made firmware updates available to resolve this vulnerability. Please
visit the following location to obtain the firmware updates:

www.hp.com/go/ilo

HISTORY
Version:1 (rev.1) - 17 March 2015 Initial release

